<p>Several responses to the letter were published, including one from Bill Gates.</p>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFHayes1976">Hayes, Mike (February 1976). "<a href="http://www.digibarn.com/collections/newsletters/homebrew/V2_02/index.html" class="external text" title="http://www.digibarn.com/collections/newsletters/homebrew/V2_02/index.html" rel="nofollow">Regarding Your Letter of February 3</a>". <i>Homebrew Computer Club Newsletter</i> (Mountain View, CA: Homebrew Computer Club) <b>2</b> (2): p. 2<span class="printonly">. <a href="http://www.digibarn.com/collections/newsletters/homebrew/V2_02/index.html" class="external free" title="http://www.digibarn.com/collections/newsletters/homebrew/V2_02/index.html" rel="nofollow">http://www.digibarn.com/collections/newsletters/homebrew/V2_02/index.html</a></span>.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Regarding+Your+Letter+of+February+3&amp;rft.jtitle=Homebrew+Computer+Club+Newsletter&amp;rft.aulast=Hayes&amp;rft.aufirst=Mike&amp;rft.au=Hayes%2C+Mike&amp;rft.date=February+1976&amp;rft.volume=2&amp;rft.issue=2&amp;rft.pages=p.+2&amp;rft.place=Mountain+View%2C+CA&amp;rft.pub=Homebrew+Computer+Club&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.digibarn.com%2Fcollections%2Fnewsletters%2Fhomebrew%2FV2_02%2Findex.html&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Open_Letter_to_Hobbyists"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span></li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li><cite style="font-style:normal" class="" id="CITEREFWarren1976"><a href="/wiki/Jim_Warren" title="Jim Warren">Warren, Jim C.</a> (July 1976). "Correspondence". <i>SIGPLAN Notices</i> (ACM) <b>11</b> (7): p. 1.</cite><span class="Z3988" title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=article&amp;rft.atitle=Correspondence&amp;rft.jtitle=SIGPLAN+Notices&amp;rft.aulast=Warren&amp;rft.aufirst=Jim+C.&amp;rft.au=Warren%2C+Jim+C.&amp;rft.date=July+1976&amp;rft.volume=11&amp;rft.issue=7&amp;rft.pages=p.+1&amp;rft.pub=ACM&amp;rfr_id=info:sid/en.wikipedia.org:Open_Letter_to_Hobbyists"><span style="display: none;">&#160;</span></span> Jim Warren, the editor of <a href="/wiki/Dr._Dobbs_Journal" title="Dr. Dobbs Journal" class="mw-redirect">Dr. Dobbs Journal</a>, describes how the <a href="/wiki/Tiny_BASIC" title="Tiny BASIC">Tiny BASIC</a> project is an alternative to hobbyist "ripping off" software.</li>
</ul>
